a
spread results in a cash inflow to the spread strategist, the spread is a credit spread.
a
This merely means that the sell side ofthe spread brings in a higher price than is paid
for the buy side ofthe spread. Ifthe reverse is true — that is, there is a cash outflow
:
from the spread transaction — the spread is said to be a debit spread. This means that
/
the buy side of the spread costs more than is received from the sell side. It is also
:
common to refer to the purchased side ofthe spread as the long side and to refer to
i
the written side ofthe spread as the short side.
