.
option market, it was often stated that the reason for this relationship was that the
F
demand for calls was larger than the demand for puts. This may have been partially
=
_ true, but certainly it is no longer true in the listed option targets, wherea large sup-
___ ply of both listed puts and calls is available through the OCC. Arbitrageurs again
