~ anywhere below 50, the October 50 will have some value and the investor will be able
| __ to recover something from the position. This is distinctly different from the original
a
put holding of the October 45, whereby the maximum loss would be incurred unless
| ___ the stock were below 45 at expiration. Thus, the introduction of the spread also
| ___ reduces the chances ofhaving to realize the maximum loss.
p
In summary, the put holder faced with an unrealized loss may be able to create
|__ aspread by selling twice the number ofputs that he is currently long and simultane-
