nificant assumption that volatility and interest rates are unchanged). If XYZ trades
higher than 110, the diagonal spread will lose some of its profit; in fact, ifXYZ were
to trade at a very high price, the diagonal spread would actually havea loss (see Table
25-4). Whenever the purchased LEAPS call loses its time value premium, the diag-
