The new divisor is calculated by dividing the new sum ofthe prices, 125, by the
old closing price, 102.51. Thus the divisor is reduced in order to produce the same
index value — 102.51 — even though the sum of the prices of the stocks in the index
is now 125 instead of the previous 170. Note that the new divisor is not dependent
on the old divisor.

