italization of the portfolio.
4.
Divide the sum from step 3 by the index price of the futures to be used and the
unit of trading for the futures ($500 per point for the S&P 500 futures) to deter-
mine how many futures to sell.
Example: Suppose that one owns a portfolio of three diverse stocks: 3,000 GOGO,
an over-the-counter technology stock; 5,000 UTIL, a major public utility stock; and
