he gets more downside protection, but his upside is even more limited than it pre
ously was. Still, if he is worried about the stock falling lower, this may be a prop
A
action to take. Conversely, if the common is rallying, and the covered writer is mo
i
bullish on the stock, he can roll up in order to increase his upside profit potential
ae
course, by rolling up, he creates more downside risk ifthe common stock should su
