Equivalent Positions
Some strategies can be constructed with either puts or calls to attain the same prof-
it potential. These are called equivalent strategies and are given in Table B-1. They
do not necessarily have the same potential returns, because the investment required
may be quite different. However, equivalent positions have profit graphs with exact-
ly the same shape.
Other equivalences can be determined by combining any two strategies in the
left-hand column and setting that combination equivalent to the two corresponding
strategies in the right-hand column.
